This paper deals with community detection in multilayer networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper deals with detecting communities in networks. The second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper uses a variational Bayes approach for inferring hidden communities. The third likely sub-category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper proposes a method for detecting communities in networks. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper deals with algorithms for community detection. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper uses a probabilistic model for community detection.
